<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="422" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.248/251: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-23T19:00:00-05:00">October 23, 1941—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>417. Your 566, October 22, 8 p.m. Your suggestions are being very
                            carefully studied on an urgent basis, and it is hoped that something can
                            be worked out in time to permit of an announcement during the course of
                            Larco Herrera’s visit to Washington. In the meantime, of course, no
                            commitment can be made.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>